    • Method Detail

      • getEncoderTicksPerUnit

        public double getEncoderTicksPerUnit()
        Get the number of encoder ticks per revolution of the wheel. This is roughly equal to the number of encoder ticks per rev * the wheel diameter * pi.
        Returns:
        The number of encoder ticks in native units.

      • setEncoderTicksPerUnit

        public void setEncoderTicksPerUnit(double encoderTicksPerUnit)
        Set the number of encoder ticks per unit distance travelled by the wheel. You can calculate this by doing the number of encoder ticks per rev * the wheel diameter * pi.
        Parameters:
        encoderTicksPerUnit - The number of encoder ticks in native units.

      • getEncoderTickRatio

        public double getEncoderTickRatio()
        Get the ratio of encoder ticks to distance travelled by the wheel. Multiply this number by a number of encoder ticks to get the distance travelled by the wheel.
        Returns:
        The ratio in encoder ticks / unit used in the Trajectory.

        public void setGetEncoderVelocityFunction(DoubleSupplier getEncoderVelocityFunction)
        Sets the function that sets the encoder velocity. This function will be passed the velocity in native units / decisecond.
